review_blob: Bottle from Sklavenitis Hypermarket (Athens, Greece). Very watery with no aroma. Medium sweet taste.
Bottle. Hops, citrus and lemon athe taste, with beautyful aftertaste. Easy drinking but too complex aroma! Yes...Its the aroma I loved.
Bottle. Nice brown head, but didnt last too much. Strong (greek!) coffee and smoke aroma. Same at the powerful taste. Like the long lasting bitter finish.
Bottle from beer-shop.gr. Aroma: pines, cool forest herbs, grapefruit, hops. Flavor is moderate to heavy sweet and bitter, pine needles, hops, very light. Quite nice beer.
Bottle @The Local Pub. Strong coffee aroma, espresso and brown sugar in the taste. Very very good stuff.
Bottle from beer-shop.gr. Nose of lemon and light tropical fruits, flavor is fruity and bitter. Pretty strong carbonation. Very easily drinkable. A refreshing heavily hopped IPA.
500 ml bottle. Nicely balanced taste, light sweet and light bitter with notes of chocolate, licorice and dark fruit. Smooth and creamy texture, full body, fine to average carbonation. Like!

On tap @The Local Pub. A delicious, tasty, hoppy pale ale! Has a fruity malty piney hoppy aroma. Big pine kick in the taste , well carbonated, nice sweetish bitterness in the finish, gets better as it warms.
Strong and nice aroma of fresh fruits and bread. Nice balanced taste not too much bitter neither sweet. The finish is bitter. I liked it a lot for the aroma. it makes you want more and more!
beer_name: Fresh Chios Beer / Frskia Mpra Chou (House Ale)

review_blob: Pours brown with a thick tan head. Aroma is malty and slightly sweer. Flavor has good roasty malts, light fruit. Liked it a lot. Want to drink it again and again!
Watery body. Sweet flavor with notes of caramel. Not anything else. No aroma, no aftertaste, nothing to remind you that you are drinking a pilsener.
A dark Bire de Garde.  Creamy off white head. Aroma of spices and earth. Sweet flavour with notes of caramel and spices.
Big white head. Aroma has floral hoppy notes but very powerful. Nice carbonation. Not an IPA but a belgian style...hopped beer.
Golden color, low carbonation, light taste, light aroma, everything is light...In a hot Greek day, better drink a glass of water.
Goes down very well. Light smoke taste and aroma. Light body. Didnt find the standard characteristics of a wheat beer in the mouth neither in the nose.
Wood and bacon in the taste and the aroma. Also,caramel malts and smoke (a little BBQ). The beer that comes in my mind when I think about Rauchbiers.
Clear golden color, small white head, light bitter taste. Enjoyed it in a hot greek summer. Really liked it!

beer_brewer_name: Brouwerij der Trappistenabdij De Achelse Kluis
review_blob: Caramel, herbs, brown foam, medium sweetness and bitterness, heavily sour, soft carbonation, sticky.
